<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861230-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Gates Postpones Unit's Sale</HL><DD> 12/30/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GLJTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Gates Corp. said its agreement to sell its 64.8% stake in its Gates Learjet Corp. unit to Cobey Corp. by year-end has been postponed.    Gates, a closely held concern with interests in automotive and industrial parts, said the schedule of its $62.7 million sales agreement with Boston-based Cobey hadn't been met, but that discussions would continue concerning a sale next year.    Earlier this month, Gates said an agreement to sell Tucson, Ariz.-based Gates Learjet to M.J. Rosenthal andamp; Associates Inc., a New York investment firm, was terminated by &quot;mutual consent.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>